def load_my_data(your_local_path, filename):
    return (pd.read_table(your_local_path+filename))

# Name of the file we are using.
file1 = 'pseudo_facebook.tsv'

# Loading the data using function created earlier
fbd = load_my_data(your_local_path,file1)

<font color=Blue> UpX_Facebook Dataset - Attribute Info </font>¶

userid: ID of user age: User's age (years) dob_day: Day of date of birth (1-31) dob_year: Year of date of birth dob_month: Month of date of birth gender: M/F tenure: How long have facebook user been on site friend_count: Total number of friends friendships_initiated: Friend requests sent likes: Total number of likes by user likes_received: Total number of likes received by user mobile_likes: Number of likes by user (through mobile) mobile_likes_received: Number of likes received by user (through mobile) www_likes: Number of likes by user (through desktop website) www_likes_received: Number of likes received by user (through desktop)

<font color=Blue> UpX_Facebook Dataset - Area of Analysis </font>¶

-> Date of Birth (Age) Analysis -> Friend-Count Analysis -> Tenure Analysis -> Like Analysis

# Defining function to find outliers from facebook dataset.
def detect_outliers(col,length):
    q1 = np.percentile(fbd[col],25)
    q3 = np.percentile(fbd[col],75)
    IQR = q3-q1
    
    # outlier step
    outlier_step = 1.5*IQR
  
    # Determining the list of indices of outliers for each feature column.
    outlier_list_col = fbd[(fbd[col] < q1 - outlier_step) | (fbd[col] > q3 + outlier_step)].index
  
    return outlier_list_col

# Categorically, age has been grouped in age_group column into child, teenagers, youngsters, adolescents, adults, mid-aged and senior-citizen based on some assumptions.
def age_group(row):
  if row['age'] < 13 :
     return 'Children'
  if row['age'] >= 13 and row['age'] < 20 :
     return 'Teenagers'
  if row['age'] >= 20 and row['age'] < 26 :
     return 'Youngsters'
  if row['age'] >= 26 and row['age'] < 31:
     return 'Adolescents'
  if row['age'] >= 31 and row['age'] < 41:
     return 'Adults'
  if row['age'] >= 41 and row['age'] < 61:
     return 'Mid-Aged'
  if row['age']  >= 61:
     return 'Senior-Citizen'
    
fbd['Age_Group'] = fbd.apply(lambda row: age_group(row),axis=1)
fbd.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
fbd.info()

# infant (birth-12 months)
# toddler (1-4 years)
# child (5-11 years)
# preteen (12 years)
# teenager (13-19 years)
# youngster (20-25 years)
# adolescents (26-30 years)
# adult (31-40 years)
# mid-aged (41-60 years)
# senior citizen (60+ years)

# Conversion of tenure column into Year groups for better visualization and analysis.
def Tenure_Year(row):
  if row['tenure'] <= 365 :
     return '1 year'
  if row['tenure'] > 365 and row['tenure'] <= 730 :
     return '2 year'
  if row['tenure'] > 730 and row['tenure'] <= 1095 :
     return '3 years'
  if row['tenure'] > 1095 and row['tenure'] <= 1460 :
     return '4 years'
  if row['tenure'] > 1460 and row['tenure'] <= 1825 :
     return '5 years'
  if row['tenure'] > 1825 and row['tenure'] <= 2190 :
     return '6 years'
  if row['tenure'] > 2190 and row['tenure'] <= 2555 :
     return '7 years'
  if row['tenure'] > 2555:
     return '8+ years'
  
fbd['Tenure_Year'] = fbd.apply(lambda row: Tenure_Year(row),axis=1)
fbd.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
fbd.info()
